# .vercelignore — files NOT uploaded to Vercel during deploy.
#
# Vercel runs `pnpm install` + `pnpm build` inside its own builder, so
# anything Next.js needs at build time MUST NOT be excluded here. The
# scope is intentionally narrow: caches, test artifacts, agent state,
# audit screenshots, and editor metadata. Source code, configs, types,
# and Markdown docs all stay (the upload-size delta on docs is trivial
# and code reviewers / agents read them in-tree).
#
# Why exclude tests:
#   - `next build` only walks the App Router (`app/`) + colocated
#     components/lib; it never reads `tests/`.
#   - Vitest unit tests + Playwright e2e specs never run on Vercel —
#     they run in GitHub Actions CI.
#   - Trimming the upload speeds up cold builds (Next.js bundle output
#     is unchanged either way).
#
# Be conservative. Anything that COULD be needed at build time stays in.

# ---- Build caches / outputs ----
# Local-build artifacts; Vercel produces its own .next during deploy.
.next/
out/
*.tsbuildinfo
.turbo/
.eslintcache

# ---- Test artifacts ----
coverage/
.nyc_output/
*.lcov
playwright-report/
test-results/
.playwright/
.lighthouseci/

# ---- Tests (not used at build time on Vercel) ----
apps/web/tests/

# ---- Local pnpm store mirror ----
.pnpm-store/

# ---- IDE / OS metadata ----
.DS_Store
.idea/
.vscode/
*.log

# ---- Local agent / MCP state ----
.claude/
.playwright-mcp/

# ---- Audit / verify / walk artifacts at repo root (per .gitignore) ----
# Mirror the .gitignore patterns so a developer who staged these by
# accident never uploads them to Vercel.
audit-*.png
audit-*.jpg
audit-*.jpeg
verify-*.png
verify-*.jpg
walk-*.png
walk-*.jpg
live-*.png
live-*.jpg

# ---- Vendor docs / large-form prose ----
# Markdown docs that ship for in-repo reference (CUTOVER.md, COMPLIANCE.md,
# AUTH_CONTRACT_AUDIT.md, README.md) MUST stay — Next.js doesn't read them
# but agents and reviewers do, and the upload-size delta is tiny. Only
# the docs/reviews subtree is large enough to bother excluding.
docs/reviews/
